400
00:36:41,023 --> 00:36:46,689
In October I went a-graping to the rivermeadows, and loaded myself with clusters

401
00:36:46,689 --> 00:36:51,749
more precious for their beauty andfragrance than for food.

402
00:36:51,749 --> 00:36:59,061
There, too, I admired, though I did notgather, the cranberries, small waxen gems,

403
00:36:59,061 --> 00:37:06,639
pendants of the meadow grass, pearly andred, which the farmer plucks with an ugly

404
00:37:06,639 --> 00:37:11,018
rake, leaving the smooth meadow in a snarl,

405
00:37:11,018 --> 00:37:17,000
heedlessly measuring them by the bushel andthe dollar only, and sells the spoils of

406
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:25,065
