414
00:38:00,097 --> 00:38:07,039
It was very exciting at that season to roamthe then boundless chestnut woods of

415
00:38:07,039 --> 00:38:13,058
Lincoln--they now sleep their long sleepunder the railroad--with a bag on my

416
00:38:13,058 --> 00:38:16,019
shoulder, and a stick to open burs with in

417
00:38:16,019 --> 00:38:22,003
my hand, for I did not always wait for thefrost, amid the rustling of leaves and the

418
00:38:22,003 --> 00:38:27,099
