723
01:05:39,819 --> 01:05:48,559
logs together with a birch withe, and then,with a longer birch or alder which had a

724
01:05:48,559 --> 01:05:52,689
hook at the end, dragged them across.

725
01:05:52,689 --> 01:05:58,119
Though completely waterlogged and almost asheavy as lead, they not only burned long,

726
01:05:58,119 --> 01:06:03,059
but made a very hot fire; nay, I thoughtthat they burned better for the soaking, as

727
01:06:03,059 --> 01:06:10,379
if the pitch, being confined by the water,burned longer, as in a lamp.

728
01:06:10,379 --> 01:06:16,074
Gilpin, in his account of the forestborderers of England, says that "the

729
01:06:16,074 --> 01:06:21,949
encroachments of trespassers, and thehouses and fences thus raised on the

730
01:06:21,949 --> 01:06:25,419
borders of the forest," were "considered as

731
01:06:25,419 --> 01:06:31,759
